dealer /ˈdiːlə/

(dealers) 

1. N-COUNT A dealer is a person whose business involves buying and selling things. 商人 [商业] 

例： ...an antique dealer. …一位古董商。 

2. N-COUNT A dealer is someone who buys and sells illegal drugs. 毒品贩子 

例： They will stay on the job for as long as it takes to clear every dealer from the street. 他们将坚持工作，直到街道上所有的毒品贩子都被清除。

